Privacy Policy

Last Updated: [Sep 28, 2023]

Welcome to Edustaff.in, a web portal accessible at Edustaff.in and its mobile applications, including Edustaff.in (Job Seekers Mobile App) and Edustaff.in Institutions (Recruiters Mobile App). Protecting your privacy is one of our top priorities. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how we collect and use it, and your rights regarding your data.

If you have any questions or need further information about our Privacy Policy, please feel free to contact us.

Website Address: https://www.edustaff.in

Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand how we collect, use, protect, or handle your Personally Identifiable Information (PII) in accordance with our website and mobile applications.

Collection of Information

Personal Data

As a Job Seeker, when you register with us, we may ask for your Personal, Educational, Professional, and Communication information, including email address and mobile number. You may also choose to upload files (resumes and videos), as well as a profile photo and demo/introduction videos. Your location will be shared with recruiters, parents, and students seeking tuition services.

As a Recruiter, you will provide your institution's communication details, including personal and official contact numbers, videos, institution location, and email ID. Additionally, you will share job vacancy information. This information is made available to Job Seekers.

IP Address

For security purposes, we record your IP address during login, registration, and data modification. This information is kept private.

Open ID / OAuth / Service Provider Login

When you log in using Open ID / OAuth 2.0 (Google, Yahoo, Facebook, Microsoft), your email ID and password are sent directly to the respective provider for authentication. Your email ID is sent to us only after successful authentication.

How We Use Your Information

Recruiters use the information to search for and contact Job Seekers about job opportunities.
Job Seekers search and apply for posted job notifications and view contact information and institution details shared by recruiters.
Our automated systems and support team members locate candidate profiles and send job offer notifications through SMS, email, and app push notifications.
We do not sell your data to third parties, except for the specified use cases mentioned above.
Your Rights Over Your Data

As a Job Seeker, you have control over your profile visibility through the Settings page in our app. You can deactivate your profile to stop receiving notifications. This does not affect data we must retain for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Data Protection Measures

We conduct regular Malware & Virus Scanning.
Your password is stored in an irreversible encrypted format.
Your personal information is stored behind secured networks, accessible only by authorized personnel who are bound by confidentiality. All supplied information is encrypted using Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology.
We do not store sensitive data like credit card or debit card numbers. All transactions are processed through secure gateways and are not stored on our servers.
GDPR Data Protection Rights

We want you to be aware of your data protection rights:

The right to access: You can request copies of your personal data.
The right to rectification: You can request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete information.
The right to erasure: You can request the deletion of your personal data under certain conditions.
The right to restrict processing: You can request restrictions on the processing of your personal data under certain conditions.
The right to object to processing: You can object to the processing of your personal data under certain conditions.
The right to data portability: You can request the transfer of your collected data to another organization or directly to you under certain conditions.
If you wish to exercise any of these rights or have questions, please contact us.

We have taken utmost care to secure your data and do not store credit card, debit card numbers, or any other sensitive data.
